window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>From </b><b><i>Leviathan Wakes</i></b><b> to </b><b><i>Leviathan Falls</i></b><b>, James S. A. Corey's Hugo Award-winning Expanse series has redefined modern space opera.&nbsp;</b></p> <p>On Mars, a scientist experiments with a new engine that will one day become the drive that fuels humanity's journey&nbsp;into the stars.&nbsp;</p> <p>On an asteroid station, a group of prisoners are oblivious to the catastrophe that awaits them.&nbsp;</p> <p>On a future Earth beset by overpopulation, pollution, and poverty, a crime boss desperately seeks to find a way off planet.</p> <p>On an alien world, a human family struggles to establish a colony and make a new home.</p> <p>All these stories and more are featured in this unmissable collection of short fiction&nbsp;set in the hardscrabble world of The Expanse.</p> <p><b>Contents:</b></p> <p><b>The Expanse Short Fiction</b></p> <p><i>Drive</i></p> <p><i>The Butcher of Anderson Station</i></p> <p><i>The Churn</i></p> <p><i>Gods of Risk</i></p> <p><i>The Vital Abyss</i></p> <p><i>Strange Dogs</i></p> <p><i>Auberon</i></p> <p><i>The Sins of our Fathers</i></p>"; 
